PIP(1)                                pip                               PIP(1)

NNAAMMEE
       pip - package manager for Python packages

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       pip <command> [options]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       pip is the PyPA recommended package manager for Python packages

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       --hh,, ----hheellpp
              Show help.

       ----iissoollaatteedd
              Run  pip in an isolated mode, ignoring environment variables and
              user configuration.

       --vv,, ----vveerrbboossee
              Give more output. Option is additive, and can be used  up  to  3
              times.

       --VV,, ----vveerrssiioonn
              Show version and exit.

       --qq,, ----qquuiieett
              Give  less  output.  Option is additive, and can be used up to 3
              times (corresponding to WARNING,  ERROR,  and  CRITICAL  logging
              levels).

       ----lloogg <<ppaatthh>>
              Path to a verbose appending log.

       ----pprrooxxyy <<pprrooxxyy>>
              Specify a proxy in the form [user:passwd@]proxy.server:port.

       ----rreettrriieess <<rreettrriieess>>
              Maximum  number  of  retries each connection should attempt (de-
              fault 5 times).

       ----ttiimmeeoouutt <<sseecc>>
              Set the socket timeout (default 15 seconds).

       ----eexxiissttss--aaccttiioonn <<aaccttiioonn>>
              Default action when a path already exists:  (s)witch,  (i)gnore,
              (w)ipe, (b)ackup, (a)bort).

       ----ttrruusstteedd--hhoosstt <<hhoossttnnaammee>>
              Mark this host as trusted, even though it does not have valid or
              any HTTPS.

       ----cceerrtt <<ppaatthh>>
              Path to alternate CA bundle.

       ----cclliieenntt--cceerrtt <<ppaatthh>>
              Path to SSL client certificate, a  single  file  containing  the
              private key and the certificate in PEM format.

       ----ccaacchhee--ddiirr <<ddiirr>>
              Store the cache data in <dir>.

       ----nnoo--ccaacchhee--ddiirr
              Disable the cache.

       ----ddiissaabbllee--ppiipp--vveerrssiioonn--cchheecckk
              Don't periodically check PyPI to determine whether a new version
              of pip is available for download. Implied with --no-index.

       ----nnoo--ccoolloorr
              Suppress colored output

CCOOMMMMAANNDDSS
       ppiipp--iinnssttaallll((11))
              Install packages.

       ppiipp--ddoowwnnllooaadd((11))
              Download packages.

       ppiipp--uunniinnssttaallll((11))
              Uninstall packages.

       ppiipp--ffrreeeezzee((11))
              Output installed packages in requirements format.

       ppiipp--lliisstt((11))
              List installed packages.

       ppiipp--sshhooww((11))
              Show information about installed packages.

       ppiipp--cchheecckk((11))
              Verify installed packages have compatible dependencies.

       ppiipp--sseeaarrcchh((11))
              Search PyPI for packages.

       ppiipp--wwhheeeell((11))
              Build wheels from your requirements.

       ppiipp--hhaasshh((11))
              Compute hashes of package archives.

       ppiipp--hheellpp((11))
              Show help for pip commands.

AAUUTTHHOORR
       pip developers

